,Another way to say the same thing: there are no instructions that take two arbitrary effective addresses for operands. The `mod/rm` encoding is designed for one register operand (3 bits) and one `r/m` operand (2 bits to encode the addressing mode (where register direct is one of the options), and 3 bits for the register, or another whole byte for addressing modes with an index register.
